Memo: Scope: The installation of 2 pressurized gas lines. The first is a ¾” copper argon line to be installed from the argon bottle pack location to elevation near ceiling height trough 2 building walls ending at the column specified at time of walk through. The argon line will terminate at each end with a threaded ball valve with the column line drop to include a regulator as well. Both drops will be at approximately 6’-0” AFF. The second line will be a ¾” carbon steel propane line to be installed from the tank location mirroring the routing of the argon line. The propane line will also terminate at both ends with a threaded ball valve along with a regulator at the point of use location at the column line. Both ends of the propane line will also be at approximately at 6’-0” AFF.
